author: COMSOL
description: Resistive power dividers and T-junction power dividers are two conventional types of three-port power dividers. Such dividers are either lossy or not matched to the system reference impedance at all ports. In addition, isolation between two coupled ports is not guaranteed. The Wilkinson power divider outperforms both the lossless T-junction divider and the resistive divider and does not have the issues mentioned above. This example shows how to model such a device.
label: wilkinson_power_divider.mph
